title: Fernhill — RESTART reboots the story (ADR-248 acceptance)
story: fernhill
description: The original Chord-path restart repro (restart used to throw
  "assignRoom: room 'r01' not found" under the hood and render as
  "I don't understand that."). Under ADR-248 the client/harness reboots
  with a fully fresh ChordStory rebuilt from source, so restart acks and
  the opening state comes back clean.
---

# Establish position away from the opening room
> look
[OK: contains "Iron Gates"]

> north
[OK: contains "Gravel Drive"]

# Restart: the ack renders (never "I don't understand that."), then the
# harness reboots onto a fresh ChordStory
> restart
[OK: contains "The story restarts."]
[OK: not contains "I don't understand"]
[OK: not contains "Restart failed"]

# Fresh boot: back at the opening location, world fully rebuilt
> look
[OK: contains "Iron Gates"]

# The rebuilt world plays normally
> north
[OK: contains "Gravel Drive"]
